	(302,6,'2017-03-14 10:58:43','2017-03-14 10:58:43','Bob Smith has been in the professions finance sector for over 25 years and is an experienced area sales manager covering  the midlands area.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFounded in 1992 Braemar Finance was acquired by Close Brothers Group plc in 2000 and are one of the leading providers of finance to the professions in the UK. As a direct funder with a wealth of experience of tailor-made solutions designed  to assist your dental business the team fully understand the pressures of a modern practice and the time pressures that principals and associates find themselves under today.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBob  will be talking about the financial advantages of investing in equipment, and the reason why you should use finance as a tax efficient method to acquire the latest digital pieces of technology available in the sector that your practice needs.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAnnual Investment Allowance (AIA) is not as frightening as people think, in fact it can be straightforward, and beneficial to your tax status if used correctly. The upper limit in any one financial year is £200,000 and tax relief is received in the year of purchase rather than over several years.  This alone can generate a significant cash flow benefit for your business.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn this presentation we will explore what other practice builders can you use to help fund your investment? The benefits of offering enhanced services to ensure you utilise your newly acquired equipment as a means to enhance your cash flow.','Bob Smith: How to finance a digital practice','','draft','closed','closed','','braemar-finance-speaker-how-to-finance-a-digital-practice','','','2017-09-22 15:11:25','2017-09-22 14:11:25','',0,'http://localhost/?post_type=speakers&#038;p=302',0,'speakers','',0),
