	(722,6,'2017-07-16 15:22:50','2017-07-16 14:22:50','Peter’s career in Dentistry started 15 years ago in marketing with “Kodak Dental Systems.”\r\n\r\nHe started 360 Visualise 7 years ago as a specialist CBCT scanning centre. As the technology evolved and the equipment has become more affordable 360 Visualise started selling 3D CBCT and other digital equipment. Last year 360 Visualise were Carestream’s largest independent dealer, as well as being authorised Planmeca dealers. As well as selling CBCT 360 Visualise also offer a rental scheme.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nToday 360 Visualise take over 150 referred scans a month and work along side some of the UK’s most influential digital dentists. 360 Visualise have just started to offer an intra oral scanning service, and are constantly being pushed and tested by their referring practitioners to be able to squeeze more and more value from the data these devices now give us. 360 Visualise are currently working on an education course plan for 2018. Helping you to find innovative ways to print guides and use new crown down digital implant planning techniques.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEvery practitioner’s wish list and individual needs from their CBCT are different. In this presentation we will explore some of the most popular features and explain their benefits and how they might fit into your overall workflow.','Peter Donnelly: Digital X-ray & CBCT Scanner','','draft','closed','closed','','peter-donnelly-digital-x-ray-cbct-scanner','','','2017-09-22 15:11:58','2017-09-22 14:11:58','',0,'http://localhost/?post_type=speakers&#038;p=722',0,'speakers','',0),
	(723,6,'2017-07-16 15:23:35','2017-07-16 14:23:35','3D printing takes the efficiencies of digital design to the production stage. By combining oral scanning, CAD/CAM design and 3D printing, dental laboratories can accurately and rapidly produce crowns, bridges, stone models and a range of orthodontic appliances. ','Hugo Patrao: 3D Printers','','draft','closed','closed','','hugo-patrao-3d-printers','','','2017-09-22 15:11:36','2017-09-22 14:11:36','',0,'http://localhost/?post_type=speakers&#038;p=723',0,'speakers','',0),
	(724,6,'2017-06-16 15:26:42','2017-06-16 14:26:42','Chris Lefkaditis is the principal of a private practice in Norwich. He qualified as a BSC Dental scientist in 1989. He later joined dental school and graduated as a dental surgeon with honours in 1995 from the University of Pretoria, South Africa. In 1999 he was awarded a Postgraduate higher Diploma in Dentistry (oral and maxillofacial surgery), which he again graduated with honours. He established a referral centre in Norfolk for oral surgery, sedation and dental implants. He has extensive experience in implant dentistry and his special interests include Cosmetic and Implant Dentistry. He has been placing implants since 1999.\r\nHis vast experience in digital dentistry includes CadCam Dentistry and Computer Guided Implantology\r\n\r\n• Key Opinion Leader at CEREC by Dentsply Sirona\r\n• Course Instructor at Digital Dental Academy Course\r\n\r\nHaving furthered his education in advanced implant dentistry and functional occlusion, he has taken on the role of mentoring dentists with an interest in implant dentistry and digital implantology. He is approved as a mentor by both the Association of Dental Implantology UK and the International Team for Implantology.','Chris Lefkaditis: Intraoral scanners','','draft','closed','closed','','lino-adolph-lab-equipment','','','2018-03-15 10:16:44','2018-03-15 10:16:44','',0,'http://localhost/?post_type=speakers&#038;p=724',0,'speakers','',0),
