	(1205,6,'2017-12-13 16:56:39','2017-12-13 16:56:39','Mr Patrik Zachrisson is a partner of Wensleydale Dental Practice. He graduated as a Dental Surgeon from the Karolinska Institute in Stockholm, Sweden in 1996.\r\n\r\nHe provides general dental care for a broad patient base, focusing mainly on aesthetic treatments and preventive dentistry, with a particular interest in restorative dentistry, orthodontics, implantology, digital dentistry and mentoring. He makes almost all his crown and bridgework on site in his in house dental laboratory.\r\n\r\nHe is a provider of both an NHS GDS and PDS contract and performs treatments on a Private, Denplan and NHS basis, full time.\r\n\r\nHe is also a member of the Local Dental Committee; currently the Treasurer.\r\n\r\nPatrik has been accredited a Platinum provider for Invisalign orthodontics and has earned fellowship status in the International Congress of Oral Implantologists (FICOI).\r\n\r\nHe is a mentor for the UCLan MSc course in implantology. Wensleydale Dental Practice is one of a few accepted training centres for the VSS MSc course in implantology with the <strong>University of Central Lancashire</strong><strong>.</strong>\r\n\r\nPatrik is a Key Opinion Leader with CEREC by Dentsply Sirona, a leader in digital Dental technologies.\r\n\r\nPatrik is a founding partner and course director for Digital Dental Academy, teaching and mentoring fellow dentists in advanced techniques in restorative, implant dentistry and orthodontics in digital dentistry.\r\n\r\nPatrik is also an international speaker on implants, orthodontics and digital dentistry.','Patrik Zachrisson: Digital orthodontics','','draft','closed','closed','','patrik-zachrisson','','','2018-03-15 10:17:04','2018-03-15 10:17:04','',0,'http://localhost/?post_type=speakers&#038;p=1205',0,'speakers','',0),
