nd easily. In addition to the PrograMill PM3, PM5 and PM7 machines for dental labs, Ivoclar Vivadent also offers PrograMill One, a compact milling unit that has been especially designed to meet the needs of small laboratories and dental practices.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1270\" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/PrograMill-One-1-300x284.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"284\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Scanners/CAD\r\n</strong>The range of high-end scanners from 3Shape, such as D1000 and D2000, has been extended to include the new 3Shape E series. Highly efficient scanning technology has been employed in this series, which comprises the three entry-level units E1, E2, and E3. Together with the software “Dental Designer” they make up a powerful package. Exclusively developed Ivoclar Digital software add-ons (Digital Press Design, Digital Denture) increase the process reliability and efficiency of fully digitized processing procedures. All 3Shape scanners and software are optimized to connect to the Ivoclar Digital system.\r\n\r\n<strong>Support services\r\n</strong>The Ivoclar Digital offering is rounded off with Service+, a dental outsourcing partner. Service+ assists dental laboratories with their entry into the world of CAD/CAM fabrication by taking on design and production orders and providing dental laboratories with access to an extended range of materials and indications. Therefore, laboratories benefit from enhanced productivity and even more flexibility in selecting the appropriate manufacturing procedure.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Ivoclar Digital will feature at the Digital Dentistry Show in Manchester, 10th March, on dealer stands: Henry Schein and Dental Directory. For more information on the Ivoclar Digital product portfolio please visit: </em></strong><a href=\"http://www.Ivoclardigital.com\"><strong><em>www.Ivoclardigital.com</em></strong></a><strong><em>  Or contact a Digital Product Specialist: </em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong><em>Midlands and North - Tom Rolling 07817 441320 </em></strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong><em>South and Ireland - Vicken Hatsakordzian 07772 746780</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>','Ivoclar Vivadent contributes to shaping the future of digital prosthetics','','inherit','closed','closed','','1267-revision-v1','','','2018-02-08 08:50:14','2018-02-08 08:50:14','',1267,'http://localhost/1267-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(1276,6,'2018-02-08 08:52:23','2018-02-08 08:52:23','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1245\" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Marco-Heidel.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"602\" height=\"462\" />\r\n\r\nThe Digital Dentistry Show is excited to announce Marco Heidel has been added to the speaker-line up for Digital Dentistry Show North, Manchester, on the 10th March 2018. He will be lecturing on Computer Dental Diagnostic, covering everything you need to know on the topic.\r\n\r\nDealing with accuracy, reliability and productivity is a challenge for all teams. Marco Heidel, MDT. (Zirkonzahn), will explain the modern concept of Computer Dental Diagnostic. By demonstrating patient cases, he will perform an in-depth analysis of the latest state-of-the-art devices for a smooth, individual workflow, from digital patient analysis to the final restoration. Marco will show a revolutionary approach to capture the patient’s reference planes and to reproduce 1:1 analogue data into the software through a photo-realistic 3D digitisation of the patient’s face, resulting in a 100% individual and reproducible restoration. This method permits to work on the always-accessible virtual patient reducing the error rate and the number of meetings at the practice. A new computer-based guided implant planning solution allowing for backward planning and the following immediate loading of implants will also be outlined.\r\n<h3>About Marco:</h3>\r\n<strong>Since August 2016</strong>\r\nSteger dental laboratory (Zirkonzahn), Brunico, Italy.\r\nCourse instructor in practical and digital dental technology in South Tyrol and worldwide.\r\nResearch and development collaborator.\r\n\r\n<strong>2014 – 2015</strong><strong>\r\n</strong>Master school of dental technology, Erfurt, Germany\r\nTraining as master dental technician, technical commercial-craft and trainer\r\n\r\n<strong>2010 – 2014</strong>\r\n“Pötzsch” dental laboratory, Dresden, Germany\r\nDental technician in all dental technical fields, CAD/CAM, organisation-planning-consultation\r\n\r\n<strong>2008 – 2009</strong>\r\nLuciano Gaddi dental laboratory, Reggio Emilia, Italy\r\nCAD/CAM, aesthetic and functional all-ceramic restorations and implant restorations\r\n\r\n<strong>2008</strong>\r\nMy Dental laboratory, Altenberg, Germany\r\nDental technician in all technical fields and CAD/CAM\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/register/\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1263\" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/DDS-Register-for-free-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"200\" /></a>','New speaker!','','inherit','closed','closed','','1247-revision-v1','','','2018-02-08 08:52:23','2018-02-08 08:52:23','',1247,'http://localhost/1247-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
