	(1475,6,'2018-07-16 10:01:51','2018-07-16 09:01:51','The advent of 3D imaging in dentistry has seen a surge in the use of drilling guides to help surgeons place dental implants with increased accuracy and safety. Dynamic Navigation takes guided surgery to another dimension. David Burgess will introduce you to the world of true dynamic   guidance during freehand implant site preparation and placement, and show how he has managed to achieve consistent accuracy and a higher level of safety. The latest revolutionary development in Dynamic Navigation, Trace and Place, gives surgeons the distinct advantage of having computer guidance without the need for any appliance, stent or guide in the mouth. David’s overview of Dynamic Navigation will cover single implants to full arch cases, and show Trace and Place in action.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"Body\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Having graduated from the University of Manchester in 1985, David placed his first dental implants in 2000. He then went on to gain post-graduate diplomas from Bristol and Newcastle Universities prior to achieving an MSc in Conscious Sedation with distinction at Newcastle in 2012. With a passion for providing the ultimate in patient care, David became a pioneer in the introduction of digital dentistry in the UK. He was the first dental surgeon in the UK to purchase 3M’s Lava Chairside Oral Scanner, and later first to upgrade to their True Definition Scanner. Having seen the benefits that digital imaging brought to every day dental practise, David became yet again the first dental surgeon in the Uk and one of the first in Europe to introduce dynamic navigation in to his implant placement protocol with ClaroNav’s Navident. David is now an established Master Clinical Trainer in dynamic navigation and, as well as running courses and master classes, he has been involved in beta testing the latest development in Navident - Trace and Place. As part of his enthusiasm for new technology, David has had numerous case studies published in UK, European and global journals detailing a range of implant procedures carried out using dynamic navigation, with several cases being world firsts. </span></p>','David Burgess: Dynamic Navigation - so much more than guided surgery - 15:30-16:00','','publish','closed','closed','','david-burgess-dynamic-navigation-much-guided-surgery','','','2018-09-11 15:08:48','2018-09-11 14:08:48','',0,'http://localhost/?post_type=speakers&#038;p=1475',0,'speakers','',0),
