	(1525,6,'2018-09-12 11:05:34','2018-09-12 10:05:34','Dealing with accuracy, reliability and productivity is a challenge for all teams. Marco Heidel, MDT. (Zirkonzahn), will explain the modern concept of Computer Dental Diagnostic. By demonstrating patient cases, he will perform an in-depth analysis of the latest state-of-the-art devices for a smooth, individual workflow, from digital patient analysis to the final restoration. Marco will show a revolutionary approach to capture the patient’s reference planes and to reproduce 1:1 analogue data into the software through a photo-realistic 3D digitisation of the patient’s face, resulting in a 100% individual and reproducible restoration. This method permits to work on the always-accessible virtual patient reducing the error rate and the number of meetings at the practice. A new computer-based guided implant planning solution allowing for backward planning and the following immediate loading of implants will also be outlined.\r\n\r\n<strong>Since August 2016</strong>\r\nSteger dental laboratory (Zirkonzahn), Brunico, Italy.\r\nCourse instructor in practical and digital dental technology in South Tyrol and worldwide.\r\nResearch and development collaborator.\r\n\r\n<strong>2014 – 2015</strong><strong>\r\n</strong>Master school of dental technology, Erfurt, Germany\r\nTraining as master dental technician, technical commercial-craft and trainer\r\n\r\n<strong>2010 – 2014</strong>\r\n“Pötzsch” dental laboratory, Dresden, Germany\r\nDental technician in all dental technical fields, CAD/CAM, organisation-planning-consultation\r\n\r\n<strong>2008 – 2009</strong>\r\nLuciano Gaddi dental laboratory, Reggio Emilia, Italy\r\nCAD/CAM, aesthetic and functional all-ceramic restorations and implant restorations\r\n\r\n<strong>2008</strong>\r\nMy Dental laboratory, Altenberg, Germany\r\nDental technician in all technical fields and CAD/CAM','Marco Heidel: Computer Dental Diagnostic - 11:00-11:30','','inherit','closed','closed','','1244-autosave-v1','','','2018-09-12 11:05:34','2018-09-12 10:05:34','',1244,'http://localhost/1244-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(1526,6,'2018-09-13 18:17:46','2018-09-13 17:17:46','','Pawel Szuba-Paszkiewicz','','inherit','open','closed','','pawel-szuba-paszkiewicz-2','','','2018-09-13 18:17:48','2018-09-13 17:17:48','',1522,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Pawel-Szuba-Paszkiewicz-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),
	(1527,6,'2018-09-13 18:17:55','2018-09-13 17:17:55','Learn about the benefits of adopting a full digital workflow for prosthodontics.  See cases from planning, intraoral scanning and completion, right through to the resulting happy patients.\r\n\r\nIn 2004 Dr. Pawel Szuba-Paszkiewicz graduated with distinction from the Faculty of Dentistry at the Medical University in Wroclaw. As a student he started to obtain his professional experience in a dental practice run by his parents, which enabled him to gain invaluable practical knowledge and skills. The skills in question, turned out to be necessary and extremely motivating while dealing with difficult clinical cases. Since 2002 Dr. Paszkiewicz has participated in many professional courses, conferences and symposia which subjects were related to the latest trends in endodontics and  prosthodontics. As far as professional development is concerned, his skills also developed in collaboration with the prestigious dental clinics in Wroclaw (Poland).\r\n\r\nCurrently, Pawel Szuba-Paszkiewicz with passion and precision carries out treatments of complex medical procedures in the field of CAD/CAM prosthodontics, full-mouth rehabilitations, and minimal-invasive aesthetic dentistry. In cooperation with Carestream Dental, Harvard Dental, Lasotronix, Cerkamed, Tokuyama Dental and OrangeDental he conducts research on the use of photoactive disinfection (PAD) in the treatment of periodontal / periapical diseases. Nowadays his professional interest are focused on Digital Dentistry with its complete workflow. He has put forward and implemented his own innovatory procedure of tissue retraction during digital prosthodontic procedures (DiaC-Traction - Diatherm-Guided Chemo-Mechanical Retraction), as well as innovative fast and complex smile designing protocol.   Apart from his work, he is a keen snowboarder and a guitar player.','Pawel Szuba-Paszkiewicz: The Prosthetic Workflow in the Digital Era - 13:30-14:00 & 16:00-16:30','','inherit','closed','closed','','1522-autosave-v1','','','2018-09-13 18:17:55','2018-09-13 17:17:55','',1522,'http://localhost/1522-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(1529,6,'2018-09-13 18:19:54','2018-09-13 17:19:54','Shaz Memon is the creative director of Digimax and Digimax Dental – a dental marketing expert agency, and has worked with leading dental and non-dental names. Digimax specialises in dental marketing, dental website design, dental SEO and dental branding. What makes Shaz Memon and Digimax Dental unique is that they can use non-dental industries to infuse creative expertise into dental marketing for their clients. Digimax’s clients include House of Fraser, McDonalds, Formula One, James Caan and Caffè Concerto. Shaz specialises in offering bespoke, creative, high-end design solutions that encompass branding, website design, top Google rankings, Emarketing and more – just for dentists. Digimax Dental is one of the world’s highest rated dental marketing agencies.','Shaz Memon: SEO Demystified - Grow your Dental Practice through Google - 12:30-13:00','','publish','closed','closed','','shaz-memon-seo-demystified-grow-dental-practice-google-1230-1300','','','2018-09-13 18:19:54','2018-09-13 17:19:54','',0,'http://localhost/?post_type=speakers&#038;p=1529',0,'speakers','',0),
